title: Show HN: Visualize the vibe of your community in real-time with AI summary
text:
For full instruction please check this page: https://www.bcad.one/project/5

We trialed it with our co-living community and we were having a great time.

It has two component - question page where users can submit and answer questions anonymously, and a vibe board where users can visualize all the answers and use AI to summarize the vibe of the community.

The intention for building this web app is not just rebuilding the Google form. We want to create an easy environment where people can do a vibe checking with their bonded community, ask the questions they always wanted to ask, and get authentic responses from other people within the community in real-time.

There are also a lot of other use cases, we'll leave it to the audience to decide.

title: Ask HN: Select Article from HN where title contains “searchTerm” and upvotes > x
text:
I am looking for an article. I remember it had a specific word in the title and a good number of upvotes and comments, but I cannot find it. HN search returns more than 10.000 results.

I should be able to find it if I could filter out articles with less than x comments or less than x upvotes.

Has anyone made such a tool?
